result.execSummary:
Phamous S Harris was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Phamous S Harris was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Amanda M. Parent in court.  Katrina Amy Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant has been turned over to the State of Mississippi on 06/19/22. On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Phamous S Harris in court with attorney Amanda M. Parent.  Defendant Phamous S Harris in custody.  Alexander C. Dyer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Phamous S Harris appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Wagner, Branch 38.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Mississippi.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.   https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/0a25f782-7319-dd31-4ed9-c0f452a2bc2b  Status conference scheduled for June 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.
